558
00:28:38,984 --> 00:28:40,284
You know who<i> that</i> is, right?

559
00:28:40,286 --> 00:28:42,786
Someone
no one's ever heard of?

560
00:28:42,788 --> 00:28:44,054
That's real good.

561
00:28:44,056 --> 00:28:45,823
I hope your parents
enjoy supporting you

562
00:28:45,825 --> 00:28:47,825
for the rest
of their lives.

563
00:28:47,827 --> 00:28:49,993
C'mon,
ritchie blackmore.

564
00:28:49,995 --> 00:28:51,328
Deep purple.

565
00:28:51,330 --> 00:28:52,830
Ohh.

566
00:28:52,832 --> 00:28:54,832
"Another brick
in the wall."

567
00:28:54,834 --> 00:28:57,000
Oh, I weep
for the future.

568
00:28:57,002 --> 00:28:58,335
[Sighs]

569
00:28:58,337 --> 00:29:00,971
Mr. mcgill,
we have a problem.

570
00:29:00,973 --> 00:29:03,907
Them.

571
00:29:05,310 --> 00:29:06,777
Hey, fellas.
Uh, you ready?

572
00:29:06,779 --> 00:29:08,178
We got the first shot
all lined up.

573
00:29:08,180 --> 00:29:10,881
Can I
walk you through it?
Uh...

574
00:29:10,883 --> 00:29:12,182
We hate
to do this to you, but...

575
00:29:12,184 --> 00:29:13,851
We're having
second thoughts.
Yeah.

576
00:29:13,853 --> 00:29:16,053
I get it. That's just nerves.
Just stage fright.

577
00:29:16,055 --> 00:29:18,088
Uh, tell you what...
We got cue cards,

578
00:29:18,090 --> 00:29:20,924
and with the magic of editing,
we're gonna make you guys

579
00:29:20,926 --> 00:29:23,160
look like James garner
and mariette hartley.

580
00:29:23,162 --> 00:29:24,361
It's not that.

581
00:29:24,363 --> 00:29:25,863
It's just that it...

582
00:29:25,865 --> 00:29:27,464
It seems like
too much money...

583
00:29:27,466 --> 00:29:29,233
For not
a whole lot of return.

584
00:29:29,235 --> 00:29:31,835
And that, my friends...
That is where you're mistaken,

585
00:29:31,837 --> 00:29:34,238
because this is about
brand awareness.

586
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:36,874
From now on,
when people think guitars,

587
00:29:36,876 --> 00:29:39,209
they're gonna think
"abq in tune."

588
00:29:39,211 --> 00:29:42,212
When they think pianos...
"abq in tune."

589
00:29:42,214 --> 00:29:44,381
Drums, xylophones...
For less than the price

590
00:29:44,383 --> 00:29:47,050
of that ritchie blackmore beauty
you got on that rack,

591
00:29:47,052 --> 00:29:50,053
you're gonna have the whole town
thinking, "abq in tune."

592
00:29:50,055 --> 00:29:51,288
Yeah, but... but
what about the time slot?

593
00:29:51,290 --> 00:29:52,956
I mean,
"murder, she wrote" repeats?

594
00:29:52,958 --> 00:29:54,258
Come on.
Come on.

595
00:29:54,260 --> 00:29:58,061
Hey, grandmas love
buying the gift of music

596
00:29:58,063 --> 00:30:00,531
