and skip, hmm?

597
00:30:00,533 --> 00:30:02,566
And it's
school-recital season,

598
00:30:02,568 --> 00:30:05,035
so where are the kids
gonna get those recorders?

599
00:30:05,037 --> 00:30:07,104
Uh, we don't sell
recorders.

600
00:30:07,106 --> 00:30:08,539
Synthesizers, then.

601
00:30:08,541 --> 00:30:10,574
But the point is,
those social security checks...

602
00:30:10,576 --> 00:30:12,376
They got
to be spent somewhere.

603
00:30:12,378 --> 00:30:13,577
Mnh.

604
00:30:13,579 --> 00:30:15,245
Hey, uh...
[Clears throat]

605
00:30:15,247 --> 00:30:17,247
As it happens,
uh, today only,

606
00:30:17,249 --> 00:30:21,251
I can, uh, offer
the same package, but...

607
00:30:21,253 --> 00:30:23,120
50% off.

608
00:30:24,522 --> 00:30:26,089
Look...

609
00:30:26,091 --> 00:30:27,925
I'm sorry,
but we can't.

610
00:30:27,927 --> 00:30:29,193
Not today,
guys.

611
00:30:29,195 --> 00:30:30,594
Don't do that.

612
00:30:30,596 --> 00:30:32,095
Guys.
Now, come on.

613
00:30:32,097 --> 00:30:33,297
Look, I know
you want this.

614
00:30:33,299 --> 00:30:35,265
I<i> know</i> you do.
50% off!

615
00:30:35,267 --> 00:30:38,602
Yeah, we get it,
but we're just not...

616
00:30:38,604 --> 00:30:41,338
Convinced.

617
00:30:41,340 --> 00:30:43,440
[Sighs]

618
00:30:43,442 --> 00:30:45,209
Free.
[Clears throat]

619
00:30:45,211 --> 00:30:47,377
I'll shoot the spot
for free.

620
00:30:48,379 --> 00:30:49,947
For free?

621
00:30:49,949 --> 00:30:52,382
You will shoot this spot
for free?

622
00:30:52,384 --> 00:30:55,352
I'll film your ad,
and I'll put it on the air.

623
00:30:55,354 --> 00:30:58,055
But when you see more traffic
coming through here...

624
00:30:58,057 --> 00:30:59,623
And you<i> will...</i>

625
00:30:59,625 --> 00:31:03,393
Then we do the other spots
for the original rate, okay?

626
00:31:03,395 --> 00:31:05,329
Now, how can you
say no?

627
00:31:05,331 --> 00:31:07,231
[Sighs]

628
00:31:07,233 --> 00:31:09,066
I mean, when he puts it
like that...
I guess we can't.

629
00:31:09,068 --> 00:31:10,367
Good.

630
00:31:10,369 --> 00:31:12,135
That's the best decision
you're gonna make.

631
00:31:12,137 --> 00:31:14,238
The... the best!

632
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:17,541
[Vehicles passing]

633
00:31:19,043 --> 00:31:22,379
[Wind whistling]

634
00:31:46,170 --> 00:31:48,472
[Sighs]

635
00:31:50,074 --> 00:31:52,676
Uh...

636
00:31:52,678 --> 00:31:55,112
You gonna catch the bus,
Mr. mcgill?

637
00:31:55,114 --> 00:31:57,347
No, I... Um...

638
00:31:57,349 --> 00:31:59,016
You guys...

639
00:31:59,018 --> 00:32:01,018
Get to
the editing room.

640
00:32:01,020 --> 00:32:04,955
I just need t...
To sit.

641
00:32:21,172 --> 00:32:23,273
Mr. mcgill?

642
00:32:24,409 --> 00:32:26,043
Oh, no.

643
00:32:26,045 --> 00:32:27,511
I-I can't.

644
00:32:27,513 --> 00:32:29,246
It's okay.

645
00:32:30,248 --> 00:32:32,049
No,
that's yours.

646
00:32:32,051 --> 00:32:34,051
You earned it.

647
00:32:34,053 --> 00:32:37,054
But you're losing money.

648
00:32:37,056 --> 00:32:39,089
We'll see.

649
00:32:39,091 --> 00:32:43,093
It...
It'll be fine.

650
00:32:43,095 --> 00:32:44,461
Okay.

651
00:32:56,240 --> 00:32:59,376
So, I finally
got my act together.

652
00:32:59,378 --> 00:33:03,714
I pulled a bunch of Alan's boxes
out of the closet.

653
00:33:03,716 --> 00:33:05,415
[Inhales sharply]

654
00:33:05,417 --> 00:33:07,484
Only took me eight years.

655
00:33:11,089 --> 00:33:14,091
I gave all of Alan's clothes
a last wash

656
00:33:14,093 --> 00:33:16,660
before driving them over
to goodwill.

657
00:33:19,097 --> 00:33:20,430
I cried.

658
00:33:20,432 --> 00:33:22,432
I cried when I washed them.

659
00:33:22,434 --> 00:33:24,434
I cried when I folded them.

660
00:33:24,436 --> 00:33:26,503
I cried when I dropped 'em off.

661
00:33:28,606 --> 00:33:32,009
But once it was done...

662
00:33:32,011 --> 00:33:34,277
It felt good...

663
00:33:34,279 --> 00:33:35,645
To let them go.

664
00:33:35,647 --> 00:33:37,447
[Man coughs softly]

665
00:33:37,449 --> 00:33:39,449
I kept his uniform, though.

666
00:33:39,451 --> 00:33:42,119
[Chuckles] Can't let<i> that</i> go.

667
00:33:42,121 --> 00:33:44,287
Lord, he'd never forgive me
if I let<i> that</i> go.

668
00:33:44,289 --> 00:33:46,623
[Laughs]

669
00:33:46,625 --> 00:33:51,294
But I figure it's okay
to keep one thing, right?

670
00:33:51,296 --> 00:33:53,463
I mean...

671
00:33:53,465 --> 00:33:57,034
People can use
the other clothes, but...

672
00:33:57,036 --> 00:34:01,071
Not sure what use they'd have
for an old uniform.

673
00:34:01,073 --> 00:34:04,307
[Vehicles passing in distance]

674
00:34:04,309 --> 00:34:07,310
I just don't remember
this much homework

675
00:34:07,312 --> 00:34:09,312
when I
was Kaylee's age.

676
00:34:09,314 --> 00:34:12,349
It doesn't seem to bother her,
but still...

677
00:34:12,351 --> 00:34:14,418
Most of it's
just busywork.

678
00:34:14,420 --> 00:34:17,788
A couple of us actually
spoke to the school board,

679
00:34:17,790 --> 00:34:19,189
and they agreed...

680
00:34:19,191 --> 00:34:20,757
Done.
All yours.

681
00:34:20,759 --> 00:34:24,227
Fair warning,
the coffee's not all that.

682
00:34:24,229 --> 00:34:25,495
[Chuckles] Mm.

683
00:34:25,497 --> 00:34:27,497
I guess they feel
if you can face this,

684
00:34:27,499 --> 00:34:29,833
you can face anything.
Could be.

685
00:34:29,835 --> 00:34:31,668
I must be stronger
than I think.

686
00:34:31,670 --> 00:34:34,671
Mm.
You mind if I ask...

687
00:34:34,673 --> 00:34:37,441
And I really don't mean
to pry, but...
let me guess.

688
00:34:37,443 --> 00:34:40,110
You have another construction
job you need my help on.

689
00:34:40,112 --> 00:34:41,411
Uh, no.

690
00:34:41,413 --> 00:34:44,514
But if I do, you'll be
the first person I call.

691
00:34:44,516 --> 00:34:47,284
[Chuckles]
Okay, ask away.

692
00:34:47,286 --> 00:34:51,221
You said you kept
your husband's uniform.

693
00:34:51,223 --> 00:34:52,856
Was he on the job?

694
00:34:52,858 --> 00:34:54,324
On the job?

695
00:34:54,326 --> 00:34:57,160
Oh, you mean
the police.

696
00:34:57,162 --> 00:34:58,695
[Chuckling] No.

697
00:34:58,697 --> 00:35:00,497
Alan was a Navy man.

698
00:35:00,499 --> 00:35:02,866
He was well out of the service
when I lost him.

699
00:35:03,868 --> 00:35:05,368
I'm sorry.

700
00:35:05,370 --> 00:35:07,704
The group has heard my story
over and over.

701
00:35:07,706 --> 00:35:11,374
Well, that's what
we're here for.

702
00:35:13,377 --> 00:35:16,546
Well...

703
00:35:16,548 --> 00:35:18,715
Alan loved to hike.

704
00:35:18,717 --> 00:35:22,385
We even opened
a camping-supply store.

705
00:35:22,387 --> 00:35:24,788
I helped him with
the mail-order side of it.

706
00:35:24,790 --> 00:35:26,723
And then, uh...

707
00:35:26,725 --> 00:35:29,793
This was
eight years ago...

708
00:35:29,795 --> 00:35:33,363
He went hiking
in gila national

709
00:35:33,365 --> 00:35:35,365
and never came back.

710
00:35:35,367 --> 00:35:37,300
They found our car,

711
00:35:37,302 --> 00:35:39,903
but they never
found him.

712
00:35:39,905 --> 00:35:41,471
And I don't know if...

713
00:35:41,473 --> 00:35:43,740
He slipped and fell
or had a heart attack

714
00:35:43,742 --> 00:35:46,910
or met someone who didn't like
the way he looked...

715
00:35:46,912 --> 00:35:48,645
I don't know.

716
00:35:48,647 --> 00:35:52,582
And even after
all these years,

717
00:35:52,584 --> 00:35:56,653
not knowing how he passed
or where he is...

718
00:35:59,724 --> 00:36:02,759
I wish
it didn't matter.

719
00:36:02,761 --> 00:36:04,928
But it does.

720
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:12,502
[Insects chirping]

721
00:36:12,504 --> 00:36:17,841
[Vehicles passing in distance]

722
00:36:27,385 --> 00:36:30,720
[Cellphone dialing]

723
00:36:37,461 --> 00:36:39,663
Pryce: Hello?

724
00:36:39,665 --> 00:36:41,398
It's me.

725
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:44,301
You make the deal?

726
00:36:44,303 --> 00:36:46,369
Uhhh, no.

727
00:36:46,371 --> 00:36:48,338
Not yet.

728
00:36:48,340 --> 00:36:49,673
Why?

729
00:36:50,675 --> 00:36:52,776
I'm in.

730
00:36:57,982 --> 00:37:00,750
[Insects chirping]

731
00:37:00,752 --> 00:37:04,921
[Vehicles passing in distance]

732
00:37:04,923 --> 00:37:07,724
[Leaves rustling]

733
00:37:10,795 --> 00:37:13,296
